entures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Murdac was born in 1266, in Cowlam, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Murdac, was 26 and her mother, Isolda of Leicestershire, was 23. She married Thomas de Boyville about 1283, in Bowland, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1326, in her hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1266–1326":"1266–1326","1264–1308":"1264–1308","1290–1360":"1290–1360","–Female":"Surnud","1240–1267":"1240–1267","1244–1267":"1244–1267","about 1283":"umbes 1283","about 1290":"umbes 1290","Aft 1267":"pärast 1267","1264":"1264","1240":"1240","1360":"1360","1290":"1290","1326":"1326","1267":"1267","1266":"1266","1244":"1244","about 1264":"umbes 1264","1308":"1308","after 1267":"pärast 1267","Cowlam, Yorkshire, England":"Cowlam, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England","England":"England","Cowland, Yorkshire, England":"Bowland, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Leicester, Leicestershire, England":"Leicester, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"1266–1326":"1266–1326","1264–1308":"1264–1308","1290–1360":"1290–1360","–Female":"Kuollut","1240–1267":"1240–1267","1244–1267":"1244–1267","about 1283":"noin 1283","about 1290":"noin 1290","Aft 1267":"1267 jälkeen","1264":"1264","1240":"1240","1360":"1360","1290":"1290","1326":"1326","1267":"1267","1266":"1266","1244":"1244","about 1264":"noin 1264","1308":"1308","after 1267":"1267 jälkeen","Cowlam, Yorkshire, England":"Cowlam, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England","England":"England","Cowland, Yorkshire, England":"Bowland, Yorksh